  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 !",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Private bus services are normal from today!",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Private buses will be in service as usual from today. It is good that it has been decided to distribute fuel to private buses indefinitely.",
        "The private bus service industry has been completely affected due to covid impact and fuel shortage. Due to fuel shortage, only 15 percent of the private buses are plying nationwide on a daily basis.",
        "Private bus owners have been queuing for days to get fuel at the Lanka IOC filling station.",
        "If you wait in line for 3 days, only 40 liters of diesel is available. From 3 days in line, only one day is covered in transport service.",
        "He said that following the continuous arrival of fuel ships to the country, fuel will be distributed indefinitely to government and private transport services, as the Ministry of Power has indicated that private buses will continue to operate as usual from today."
      ],
